  "text": "Only a few reports of Mycobacterium gastri as a cause of disseminated and pulmonary mycobacteriosis diseases in humans have been published [CITATION_1] Guerra et al., 2008) . Our study presents a first report of Mycobacterium gastri isolation in South Africa from an animal species (nyala) which presented tuberculosis -like lesions. Investigation of the pathogenic role of this NTM in animals is therefore necessary.",
